comment._content: Most likely Edward Everett Grosscup, 8/2/1860 in Bridgeton, Cumberland, NJ - 12/6/1933 in Philadelphia (darefamily.com/NJDare/d7.htm, Manual of the Legislature of New Jersey). He was chairman of the New Jersey Democratic State Committee from 1911 - 1919 (en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Jersey_Democratic_State_Committee). In 1913 he was elected State Treasurer (NYT January 29, 1913, www.mastermason.com/acacia/famous/bios/G/edward_e_grosscu...)
